  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">STAR 2-Deliver! - Quality media amplifying vulnerable citizens&apos; voices</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposal offers a multi-faceted approach to addressing access of People Living With Disabilities (PLWD) to health and education services as well as economic opportunities. It targets the stimulation of various policies/programmes and regulations whose application/enforcement have potential to improve the welfare of PLWD, that is the Disability Act, 3% DACF for PLWD, etc. These are proposed along vigorous capacity strengthening and confidence building programmes for PLWD to demand their due.
The key strategies proposed are:
i.	Capacity building for enhanced media reportage of PLWDs issues 
ii.	Mobilization and collective action to ensure systemic change on issues affecting PLWDs
iii.	Evidence based research for advocacy and citizen engagement with government
iv.	Online platform to foster citizen&#x2013;policy-maker interface</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">a-	An informed and active citizenry especially PLWDs who are able to demand their entitlements. 
b-	Improved relationships between an active media and PLWDs working together to create opportunities to dialogue with government in the formulation and implementation of social intervention policies.
c-	A set of online and digital tools deployed to sustain the drive for equal access by PLWDs to public goods and services.</narrative>
  </description>
